  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Pierce County DNA Proof of Submission

3:30 p.m.  Defendant Ryan A. Mullins in court.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Froelich - Guilty plea to charge of disorderly conduct, S/W, 1 yr probation, no specific conditions, no conditional jail time, expungement upon successful completion of probation.  Court reviews Defendant's right to an attorney.  Defendant waives his right to an attorney.  Court accepts waiver of right to attorney.    Constitutional rights explained to defendant.   Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights.   DEF PLEADS GUILTY to Count 1.    Facts are correct.    COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS.    The court finds the defendant guilty and adjudicates defendant guilty of Count 1.  Court orders S/W, 1 year probation, no specific conditions, Court costs in the amount of $443 which includes DNA surcharge, eligible for expungement upon successful completion.  Appeal rights are given to defendant.
Plea hearing on July 27, 2016 at 03:15 pm.
Plea hearing on June 7, 2016 at 04:00 pm.
Pre-trial conference on April 25, 2016 at 02:15 pm.

10:58 Defendant Ryan A. Mullins in court.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court gives constitutional rights to the court room as a group. Each Defendant in a group exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights.  Defendant has copy of complaint.  Court reads charges and possible penalties.  Defendant waives reading of the complaint. Def pleas not guilty. Court rec/enter. Froelich: $150 cash bond to remain. Def has no objection.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 25, 2016 at 02:15 pm.
